Having recently come back to the game, and having seen two expansions and numerous game changes and balancing &quot;fixes&quot; happen in this time, it floors me to see that certain evry simple thigns haven't been fixed.  VI Are You Listening? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :milaru --><img src=http://graffes.netfirms.com/smiley/milaru.gif ALT=":milaru"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   These aren't really nebulous balancing issues, these are bugfixes or &quot;obvious things&quot; IMHO:<br>
<br>
1) Harvest Slot 1 Refresh Bug - yeah you can work around it, but cmon, it's a fscking bug, fix it.<br>
<br>
2) Final Rain Wave Can't Kill Mob - it's a bug, you fixed dots, fix us.<br>
<br>
3) WK Portal Location - <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :die --><img src=http://graffes.netfirms.com/smiley/die.gif ALT=":die"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  move the freakin loc, it's just an spdat change, you dont have to move the dinky spires with it.<br>
<br>
4) Low HPS Zoning == Lose all buffs - I think if your current hps are less than your +hps from gear is the actual trigger.  You zone and you lose all buffs.  Clearly a bug.  It really hurts to lose my heavily-donated-for C3 after successfully escaping death with a gate.  With my current gear I lose buffs zoning with 2 bubbles of health, that's almost half alive for f***'s sake.  I might as well have just died, gotta buy more crack either way.<br>
<br>
5) Mob Warping to Spawn from Run Phase.  This isn't wizard specific.  In Velious, if you get a mob down to run phase and then move slightly out of range from him (somewhere around the limit of spell range), they warp back to their spawn and completely erase their memory.  Next guy to walk up and pop it gets credit for the kill.<br>
<br>
And well there's countless others but I'm done ranting and venting for now. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :crusade --><img src=http://graffes.netfirms.com/smiley/pointy.gif ALT=":crusade"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
